[22.442065, "o", "{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01XdixHeeEivFbmDs5ZwtjUr\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"1\\t/**\\n2\\t * @namespace PF.Heuristic\\n3\\t * @description A collection of heuristic functions.\\n4\\t */\\n5\\tmodule.exports = {\\n6\\t\\n7\\t  /**\\n8\\t   * Manhattan distance.\\n9\\t   * @param {number} dx - Difference in x.\\n10\\t   * @param {number} dy - Difference in y.\\n11\\t   * @return {number} dx + dy\\n12\\t   */\\n13\\t  manhattan: function(dx, dy) {\\n14\\t      return dx + dy;\\n15\\t  },\\n16\\t\\n17\\t  /**\\n18\\t   * Euclidean distance.\\n19\\t   * @param {number} dx - Difference in x.\\n20\\t   * @param {number} dy - Difference in y.\\n21\\t   * @return {number} sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy)\\n22\\t   */\\n23\\t  euclidean: function(dx, dy) {\\n24\\t      return Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);\\n25\\t  },\\n26\\t\\n27\\t  /**\\n28\\t   * Octile distance.\\n29\\t   * @param {number} dx - Difference in x.\\n30\\t   * @param {number} dy - Difference in y.\\n31\\t   * @return {number} sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) for grids\\n32\\t  "]
[22.442394, "o", " */\\n33\\t  octile: function(dx, dy) {\\n34\\t      var F = Math.SQRT2 - 1;\\n35\\t      return (dx < dy) ? F * dx + dy : F * dy + dx;\\n36\\t  },\\n37\\t\\n38\\t  /**\\n39\\t   * Chebyshev distance.\\n40\\t   * @param {number} dx - Difference in x.\\n41\\t   * @param {number} dy - Difference in y.\\n42\\t   * @return {number} max(dx, dy)\\n43\\t   */\\n44\\t  chebyshev: function(dx, dy) {\\n45\\t      return Math.max(dx, dy);\\n46\\t  }\\n47\\t\\n48\\t};\\n49\\t\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"bc8a046c-88ff-44fa-927b-7992acd1f686\",\"uuid\":\"8db875b0-edbc-48fd-a472-ab5ea503c1d4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-15T16:10:05.847Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/sagar/PathFinding.js-fork/src/core/Heuristic.js\",\"content\":\"/**\\n * @namespace PF.Heuristic\\n * @description A collection of heuristic functions.\\n */\\nmodule.exports = {\\n\\n  /**\\n   * Manhattan distance.\\n   * @param {number} dx - Difference in x.\\n   * @param {number} dy - Difference in y.\\n   * @return {number} dx + dy\\n   */\\n  manhattan: function(dx, dy) "]
[22.442443, "o", "{\\n      return dx + dy;\\n  },\\n\\n  /**\\n   * Euclidean distance.\\n   * @param {number} dx - Difference in x.\\n   * @param {number} dy - Difference in y.\\n   * @return {number} sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy)\\n   */\\n  euclidean: function(dx, dy) {\\n      return Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);\\n  },\\n\\n  /**\\n   * Octile distance.\\n   * @param {number} dx - Difference in x.\\n   * @param {number} dy - Difference in y.\\n   * @return {number} sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) for grids\\n   */\\n  octile: function(dx, dy) {\\n      var F = Math.SQRT2 - 1;\\n      return (dx < dy) ? F * dx + dy : F * dy + dx;\\n  },\\n\\n  /**\\n   * Chebyshev distance.\\n   * @param {number} dx - Difference in x.\\n   * @param {number} dy - Difference in y.\\n   * @return {number} max(dx, dy)\\n   */\\n  chebyshev: function(dx, dy) {\\n      return Math.max(dx, dy);\\n  }\\n\\n};\\n\",\"numLines\":49,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":49}}}\r\n"]
[48.535053, "o", "{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_019i4m22uxWGf8nDWBXsmSPP\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Now I have enough information to write the visual audit. Let me summarize what I've found:\\n\\n**Algorithms in src/finders:**\\n1. AStarFinder.js\\n2. BestFirstFinder.js\\n3. BiAStarFinder.js\\n4. BiBestFirstFinder.js\\n5. BiBreadthFirstFinder.js\\n6. BiDijkstraFinder.js\\n7. BreadthFirstFinder.js\\n8. DijkstraFinder.js\\n9. IDAStarFinder.js\\n10. JPFAlwaysMoveDiagonally.js\\n\\n\\n11. JPFMoveDiagonallyIfAtMostOneObstacle.js\\n12. JPFMoveDiagonallyIfNoObstacles.js\\n13. JPFNeverMoveDiagonally.js\\n14. JumpPointFinder.js (base)\\n15. JumpPointFinderBase.js (base)\\n\\n**Algorithms exposed in UI (panel.js):**\\n1. A* (with heuristic, diagonal, bi-directional, don't cross corners, weight)\\n2. IDA* (with heuristic, diagonal, don't cross corners, weight, time limit, visualize recursion) — **bug: uses `jump\\n\\n_point_heuristic` radio name instead of `ida_heuristic"]
[48.535296, "o", "`**\\n3. Breadth-First Search (diagonal, bi-directional, don't cross corners)\\n4. Best-First Search (heuristic, diagonal, bi-directional, don't cross corners)\\n5. Dijkstra (diagonal, bi-directional, don't cross corners)\\n6. Jump Point Search (heuristic, visualize recursion) — hardcoded to `IfAtMostOneObstacle`\\n7. Orthogonal Jump Point Search (heuristic, visualize recursion) — hardcoded to `Never`\\n\\n**Missing from UI:**\\n- JPFAlwaysMoveDiagonally (Always)\\n- JPFMoveDiagonallyIfNoObstacles (OnlyWhenNoObstacles)\\n- The JPS diagonal movement variants aren't fully exposed as configurable options\\n\\nI'm also spotting a critical bug where IDA* reads from the wrong radio group — it's pulling the JPS heuristic selection instead of its own dedicated `ida_heuristic` radios, so the algorithm never uses its intended heuristic. Beyond that, JPS is missing two diagonal movement modes, and the grid dimensions are locked at 64x36 with no way to adjust them.\\n\\nThe animation speed is also hardcoded to 300 operations per"]
[48.535339, "o", " second with no slider control, and when a pathfinding algorithm fails to find a route, there's no visual feedback — the stats display but the user gets no indication of failure. The parent node visualization was planned but never implemented, and JPS variants have their diagonal modes hardcoded rather than exposed to the user. The list continues with missing bi-directional support for IDA* and an incomplete thought about grid coordinate handling.\\n\\nLooking at the coordinate conversion issue, `toGridCoordinate` doesn't account for page scrolling or canvas positioning, which could cause click coordinates to be wrong if the canvas has margins or padding. There's also a selector collision where the weight spinner for IDA* uses the same `astar_weight` name attribute as the A* spinner, creating potential conflicts. The demo lacks touch event support entirely, relying only on mouse events, and the pre-built bundle used in the visual demo has no guarantee of matching the current source code. The list cuts off mid"]
[48.535352, "o", "-thought about clearing paths.\\n\\nThe \\\"Clear Walls\\\" button in ready state wipes the entire grid instead of offering a way to clear just the path while preserving walls. The stats panel has no positioned layout in CSS, so it could overlap other elements on the page. When pathfinding returns no solution, there's no error message or visual feedback—the stats just show `length: 0` and the path drawing silently returns without indicating that no path was found. I should check the CSS to see how the stats panel is positioned.\",\"signature\":\""]
